
Installing Drakon:

The program (drakon) needs to be placed in a directory that is on your
execution path.  /usr/bin or ~/bin are usually good choices.


Running Drakon:

If Drakon crashes or if you find other bugs, please check the web
page first to see if they have already been reported.


Notes on Drakon:

Drakon provides a graphical display of the processes running on your UNIX
machine.


The main web page for Drakon is

    http://www.newplanetsoftware.com/drakon/

